While in Norway üá≥üá¥ I was honored to spend a few days deep in the arctic tundra with a Sami family who allowed me to be immersed in their lives as reindeer herders (it's not an easy job!). The winter migration cabin was an hour and a half snowmobile ride into the wilderness, had no running water, electricity was ran by a generator that had to be cranked every morning and we woke up to -25 degree Celsius temperatures ‚ùÑÔ∏è The head of the household, Nils, woke up in the wee hours every morning to tend to the herd of 700 and spent the evenings chopping firewood, smoking meat and/or fetching water from the river.
